<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Training and In-service Training regarding Occupational Health and Safety </inglise>
<eesti>Sotsiaalministri 14. detsembri 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 80 </eesti>
<inglise>Regulation No. 80 of the Minister of Social Affairs of 14 December 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RTL 2000, 136, 2157), </eesti>
<inglise>(RTL (1) 2000, 136, 2157), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 1. m&auml;rtsil 2001. a., </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 1 March 2001, </inglise>
<eesti>muudetud j&auml;rgmise m&auml;&auml;rusega: </eesti>
<inglise>amended by the following Regulation: </inglise>
<eesti>27.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469. </eesti>
<inglise>27.02.2001 entered into force 17.03.2001 - RTL 2001 35, 469. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "T&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse seaduse" (RT I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362) paragrahvi 2 l&otilde;ike 3 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established on the basis of subsection 2 (3) of the Occupational Health and Safety Act (RT (2) I 1999, 60, 616; 2000, 55, 362). </inglise>
<eesti>1. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev kord reguleerib: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Procedure regulates: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmete t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalast v&auml;lja&otilde;pet ning t&auml;iend&otilde;pet; </eesti>
<inglise>1) training and in-service training regarding occupational health and safety for working environment representatives and members of working environment councils; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti t&auml;iend&otilde;pet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) in-service training for working environment specialists; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;andja (t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja) t&auml;iend&otilde;pet, kui ta t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in-service training for employers (representatives of employers) if they perform the duties of working environment specialists; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettev&otilde;ttes esmaabiandja v&auml;lja&otilde;pet ja t&auml;iend&otilde;pet; </eesti>
<inglise>4) training and in-service training for first aid providers in enterprises; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalast juhendamist ja v&auml;lja&otilde;pet t&ouml;&ouml;kohal. </eesti>
<inglise>5) instruction and training for employees regarding occupational health and safety at the workplace. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;pe koolitusasutuses </eesti>
<inglise>Training in Educational and Training Institutions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;ppe korraldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinikule ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmetele t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe hiljemalt kahe kuu jooksul alates nende valimisest v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ramisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Every employer shall organise training regarding occupational health and safety for working environment representatives and members of the working environment council not later than within two months as of their election or appointment. </inglise>
<eesti>Nende v&auml;lja&otilde;pet v&otilde;ib teha koolitaja (edaspidi koolitusasutus) 24-tunnise &otilde;ppekava alusel (lisa 1). </eesti>
<inglise>Their training may be carried out by a training provider (hereinafter educational and training institution) on the basis of a 24-hour training plan (Annex 1). </inglise>
<eesti>(27.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.02.2001 entered into force 17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinike ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmete t&auml;iend&otilde;pe korraldatakse kursusena, mille teemad ja &otilde;ppekava kinnitab koolitusasutus, l&auml;htudes t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vajadustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In-service training for working environment representatives and members of a working environment council shall be organised as a course, the topics and training plan of which shall be approved by the educational and training institution based on the needs of the employers and employees. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;andja suunab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku ja t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu liikmed t&auml;iend&otilde;ppele, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>An employer shall send the working environment representatives and the members of the working environment council on in-service training if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnas on toimunud olulisi muudatusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) significant changes take place in the working environment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;kohas vahetatakse v&otilde;i uuendatakse tehnoloogiat v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;vahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) technology or work equipment is changed or upgraded at the workplace; </inglise>
<eesti>3) t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust reguleerivates &otilde;igusaktides on toimunud olulisi muudatusi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) significant changes are made to legislation regulating occupational health and safety; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor peab seda vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a labour inspector deems it necessary; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavolinik v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnan&otilde;ukogu peab seda vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise>5) a working environment representative or the working environment council deems it necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist peab l&auml;bima t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe koolitusasutuses mitte harvem kui kord viie aasta jooksul, vajadusel ka l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1-4 nimetatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Working environment specialists shall undergo in-service training in an educational and training institution at least once every five years and, if necessary, in the cases specified in clauses (2) 1) -4). </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iend&otilde;ppe teemad valib ja &otilde;ppekava kinnitab koolitusasutus t&ouml;&ouml;andja ja t&ouml;&ouml;tajate vajadusest l&auml;htuvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>The educational and training institution shall choose the topics and approve the training plan for in-service training, based on the needs of the employers and employees. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhul kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja (t&ouml;&ouml;andja esindaja) t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialisti kohustusi ise, peab ta l&auml;bima t&auml;iend&otilde;ppe koolitusasutuses mitte harvem kui kord viie aasta jooksul, vajadusel ka l&otilde;ike 2 punktides 1-4 nimetatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If an employer (a representative of an employer) performs the duties of a working environment specialist himself or herself, he or she shall undergo in-service training in an educational and training institution at least once every five years and, if necessary, in the cases specified in clauses (2) 1) -4). </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Iga v&auml;lja&otilde;ppekursus l&otilde;peb osalejate teadmiste kontrolliga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Each basic training course shall end with an assessment of the knowledge of the participants. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Koolitusasutus peab v&auml;ljastama igale &otilde;ppekursuse l&otilde;petajale v&otilde;i &otilde;ppep&auml;eval osalejale tunnistuse, kus on m&auml;rgitud l&auml;bitud teemad ja nende mahud, tunnistuse number ja koolitusasutuse nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An educational and training institution shall issue a certificate which sets out the topics covered and the number of hours, the number of the certificate and the name of the educational and training institution to each person who has completed a training course or participated in a training day. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.02.2001 entered into force 17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Esmaabiandja v&auml;lja&otilde;pe ja t&auml;iend&otilde;pe </eesti>
<inglise>Training and in-service training for first aid providers </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;andja korraldab ettev&otilde;ttes esmaabi andvale t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe hiljemalt &uuml;he kuu jooksul alates tema m&auml;&auml;ramisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employer shall organise training for the employees providing first aid in the enterprise not later than within one month as of their appointment. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;ttes esmaabiandja v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe eesm&auml;rk on p&otilde;hiteadmiste ja praktiliste oskuste andmine kannatanu elu p&auml;&auml;stmiseks &otilde;nnetusjuhtumi korral ning esmaabi osutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The purpose of training first aid providers in an enterprise is to provide basic knowledge and practical skills for the saving of lives in the event of an accident and for the provision of first aid. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lja&otilde;ppekursuse aluseks on Eesti Punase Risti 16-tunnine &otilde;ppekava (lisa 2). </eesti>
<inglise>The 16-hour training plan of the Estonian Red Cross (Annex 2) is the basis for the basic training course. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;andja suunab esmaabiandja t&auml;iend&otilde;ppele iga kolme aasta j&auml;rel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An employer shall send first aid providers on in-service training courses once every three years. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iend&otilde;ppe eesm&auml;rk on korrata ja s&uuml;vendada v&auml;lja&otilde;ppekursusel omandatud teadmisi ja oskusi. </eesti>
<inglise>The purpose of in-service training is to review and deepen the knowledge and skills acquired during the basic training course. </inglise>
<eesti>Esmaabiandjate t&auml;iend&otilde;ppekursuse minimaalne kestus on kuus tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>The minimal duration of in-service training for first aid providers is six hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Esmaabiandjate v&auml;lja&otilde;pet ja t&auml;iend&otilde;pet koolitusasutuses v&otilde;ib l&auml;bi viia meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes on l&auml;binud Eesti Punase Risti v&otilde;i muu p&auml;deva asutuse esmaabi&otilde;petajate koolituskursuse ning omab sellekohast tunnistust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Training and in-service training for first aid providers may be carried out in an educational and training institution by medical staff who have undergone training provided by the Estonian Red Cross or another competent agency for first aid trainers and who hold a corresponding certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koolitusasutus peab kursuse l&otilde;petanud esmaabiandjale v&auml;ljastama p&auml;rast teadmiste kontrolli tunnistuse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Educational and training institutions shall issue certificates to first aid providers who complete the course, after their knowledge has been assessed. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Koolitusasutuse registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of educational and training institutions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Paragrahvi 1 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 nimetatud koolitusega v&otilde;ivad tegelda Sotsiaalministeeriumis registreeritud koolitusasutused. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Educational and training institutions registered with the Ministry of Social Affairs may engage in training specified in clauses (1) 1) -4). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Registreerimiseks esitab koolitusasutus Sotsiaalministeeriumile avalduse, milles m&auml;rgitakse &auml;ra: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to register, an educational and training institution shall submit an application to the Ministry of Social Affairs which sets out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koolitusasutuse nimi, tegevuskoha aadress ja kontaktandmed; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and address of the educational and training institution, and its contact details; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;ppekavad (teemad ja nende maht); </eesti>
<inglise>2) the training plans (the topics and the number of hours); </inglise>
<eesti>3) lektorite nimed ja kontaktandmed; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the names and contact details of the lecturers; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kasutatavate &otilde;ppematerjalide loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise>4) a list of the training materials used. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Avaldusele tuleb lisada lektorite p&auml;devust t&otilde;endavate dokumentide koopiad ja v&auml;ljastatava tunnistuse n&auml;idis. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Copies of documents certifying the competence of the lecturers and a specimen of the certificate to be issued shall be appended to the application. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Sotsiaalministeeriumi p&auml;deval ametnikul on &otilde;igus kontrollida t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu- ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusalase koolituse kvaliteeti. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Competent officials of the Ministry of Social Affairs have the right to verify the quality of training regarding occupational health and safety. </inglise>
<eesti>(27.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </eesti>
<inglise>(27.02.2001 entered into force 17.03.2001 - RTL 2001, 35, 469) </inglise>
<eesti>3. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja juhendamine ja v&auml;lja&otilde;pe t&ouml;&ouml;kohal </eesti>
<inglise>Instructing and Training Employees at Workplaces </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Sissejuhatav juhendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Introductory instruction </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja sissejuhatava juhendamise viib l&auml;bi t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnaspetsialist t&ouml;&ouml;andja kinnitatud juhendi alusel enne t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le asumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Introductory instruction shall be provided for an employee by a working environment specialist on the basis of instructions approved by the employer before the employee commenced work. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Sissejuhatav juhendamine peab sisaldama: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Introductory instruction shall include: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tte t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse, sisekorraeeskirjade ning t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoidu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutust reguleerivate &otilde;igusaktide tutvustamist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) an introduction to the organisation of the work of the enterprise and its internal procedure rules, and to legislation regulating occupational health and safety; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse tagamiseks rakendatavate abin&otilde;ude tutvustamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an introduction to the measures implemented to ensure occupational health and safety; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juhiseid k&auml;itumiseks &otilde;nnetusohu v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse korral; </eesti>
<inglise>3) instructions on how to act in the event of the risk of an accident or in the event of an accident at work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juhiseid keskkonna saastamisest hoidumiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) instructions on how to prevent the contamination of the environment; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;taja kohustusi ja &otilde;igusi vastavalt &otilde;igusaktides s&auml;testatule; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the obligations and rights of employees pursuant to the provisions of legislation; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonnavoliniku, esmaabiandja ja t&ouml;&ouml;inspektsiooni kohaliku asutuse kontaktandmete tutvustamist. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the contact details of the working environment representatives and first aid providers and the regional office of the Labour Inspectorate. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Esmajuhendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Primary instruction </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja esmajuhendamise t&ouml;&ouml;tamiskohal, kus t&ouml;&ouml;taja hakkab oma t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid t&auml;itma, viib l&auml;bi t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud p&auml;dev isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A competent person designated by the employer shall provide primary instruction for an employee at the workplace where the employee will commence performing his or her official duties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Esmajuhendamisel tutvustatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) During primary instruction, the employee shall be made aware of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt koostatud ja kinnitatud ohutusjuhendeid tehtava t&ouml;&ouml; v&otilde;i kasutatavate seadmete, masinate, t&ouml;&ouml;riistade, veokite ja muude t&ouml;&ouml;vahendite kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the safety instructions prepared and approved by the employer for the work to be performed and for the apparatus, machinery, tools, vehicles and other work equipment used; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;keskkonna ohutegureid ja vajalike isikukaitsevahendite kasutamist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the risk factors present in the working environment and the use of necessary personal protective equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ergonoomiliselt &otilde;igeid t&ouml;&ouml;asendeid ja -v&otilde;tteid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) ergonomically correct working positions and techniques; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale etten&auml;htud t&ouml;&ouml;korraldust; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the organisation of work prescribed for the employee; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tule- ja elektriohutusn&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>5) fire and electrical safety requirements; </inglise>
<eesti>6) h&auml;daabitelefoni, esmaabivahendite ja tulekustutusvahendite asukohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the location of the emergency telephone, first aid equipment and fire extinguishing equipment; </inglise>
<eesti>7) t&ouml;&ouml;kohal kasutatavaid ohum&auml;rguandeid ning evakuatsioonip&auml;&auml;sude ja -teede asukohta. </eesti>
<inglise>7) safety signs used at the workplace and the location of the emergency exits and escape routes. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;lja&otilde;pe </eesti>
<inglise>Training </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lja&otilde;pe ohutute t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tete omandamiseks korraldatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale p&auml;rast esmajuhendamist, vajadusel ka p&auml;rast t&auml;iendjuhendamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Training to acquire safe working methods shall be organised for an employee after the primary instruction and, if necessary, also after the supplementary instruction. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;lja&otilde;pe toimub t&ouml;&ouml;ajal t&ouml;&ouml;andja poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud spetsialisti v&otilde;i kogenud t&ouml;&ouml;taja juhendamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Training shall take place during working time under the supervision of a specialist or experienced employee designated by the employer. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;lja&otilde;ppe kestuse m&auml;&auml;rab t&ouml;&ouml;andja s&otilde;ltuvalt ameti- v&otilde;i kutseala spetsiifikast, keerukusest ning t&ouml;&ouml; ohtlikkusest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The employer shall determine the duration of the training depending on the specifics and complexity of the occupation or profession and the risks involved in performing the work. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) T&ouml;&ouml;taja lubatakse iseseisvale t&ouml;&ouml;le, kui juhendaja on veendunud, et t&ouml;&ouml;taja tunneb t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse n&otilde;udeid ja oskab neid praktikas rakendada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An employee is permitted to work independently if the instructor is convinced that the employee is familiar with the occupational health and safety requirements and is able to apply these in practice. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) T&ouml;&ouml;andja v&otilde;ib t&ouml;&ouml;tajale v&auml;lja&otilde;pet mitte korraldada, kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja on t&ouml;&ouml;tanud eelnevalt samalaadsel t&ouml;&ouml;l, tunneb ohutuid t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tteid v&otilde;i kui tema t&ouml;&ouml; laad seda ei n&otilde;ua. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An employer may refuse to organise training for an employee if the employee has performed similar work beforehand, is familiar with the safe working methods or if the nature of his or her work means that such training is required. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendjuhendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Supplementary instruction </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja t&auml;iendjuhendamine korraldatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Supplementary instruction shall be organised for an employee: </inglise>
<eesti>1) uute t&ouml;&ouml;tervishoiu ja t&ouml;&ouml;ohutuse juhendite v&otilde;i &otilde;igusaktide kehtestamisel v&otilde;i kehtivate n&otilde;uete muutumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) if new instructions or legislation regarding occupational health and safety is established or if the applicable requirements are amended; </inglise>
<eesti>2) t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse muutmisel v&otilde;i kui tema t&ouml;&ouml;s on olnud kolmest kuust pikem vaheaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the organisation of work is changed or if there has been a break of longer than three months in his or her work; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tehnoloogia v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;vahendite vahetamisel v&otilde;i uuendamisel; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the technology or work equipment is changed or upgraded; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&ouml;&ouml;taja &uuml;mberpaigutamisel teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le v&otilde;i tema t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete olulisel muutumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) if the employee is transferred to another position or his or her official duties change significantly; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kui t&ouml;&ouml;taja rikkus t&ouml;&ouml;ohutusn&otilde;udeid, mis p&otilde;hjustas v&otilde;i oleks v&otilde;inud p&otilde;hjustada t&ouml;&ouml;&otilde;nnetuse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) if the employee violates occupational safety requirements and so causes or could cause an accident at work; </inglise>
<eesti>6) t&ouml;&ouml;de v&otilde;i tegevuse puhul, mis ei kuulu t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;lepinguga m&auml;&auml;ratud t&ouml;&ouml;de v&otilde;i ametikohustuste hulka; </eesti>
<inglise>6) in the case of work or activities which are not included in the work or official duties of the employee determined by the contract of employment; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kui struktuuri&uuml;ksuse juht v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja ise peab seda vajalikuks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) if the head of the structural unit or the employee himself or herself deems it necessary; </inglise>
<eesti>8) kui t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor peab seda vajalikuks. </eesti>
<inglise>8) if a labour inspector deems it necessary. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iendjuhendamise sisu ja mahu m&auml;&auml;rab t&ouml;&ouml;andja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The content and amount of supplementary instruction shall be determined by the employer. </inglise>
