<eesti>Juhendamise, v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe ja iseseisvale t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamise registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of instruction, training and permission to work independently </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;taja sissejuhatav, esma- ja t&auml;iendjuhendamine, v&auml;lja&otilde;pe ning t&ouml;&ouml;taja iseseisvale t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamine registreeritakse sellekohases p&auml;evikus v&otilde;i andmebaasis, kuhu m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Introductory, primary and supplementary instruction and training provided for an employee and the fact of an employee being permitted to work independently shall be registered in the corresponding register or database which shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhendamise v&otilde;i v&auml;lja&otilde;ppe kuup&auml;ev ja kestus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date and duration of the instruction or training; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhendatava ja juhendaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning amet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the given name, surname and position of the person who received the instruction or training and of the instructor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) struktuuri&uuml;ksus, kuhu t&ouml;&ouml;taja t&ouml;&ouml;le suunati; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the structural unit to which the employee is sent to work; </inglise>
<eesti>4) t&auml;iendjuhendamise p&otilde;hjus; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the reason for supplementary instruction; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;tajale tutvustatud juhendite ja &otilde;igusaktide nimetused; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the titles of the instructions and legislation which is presented to the employee; </inglise>
<eesti>6) iseseisvale t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamise kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the date on which the employee is permitted to work independently. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;taja kinnitab l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juhendamist, v&auml;lja&otilde;pet ning iseseisvale t&ouml;&ouml;le lubamist oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Employees shall confirm the instruction, training and permission to work independently specified in subsection (1) by their signature. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
